.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH k2i-maintenance 1  "k2i-maintenance "
.SH NAME
k2i\-maintenance \- Run maintenance tasks manually
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBk2i\-maintenance\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Run maintenance tasks manually
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
k2i\-maintenance\-compact(1)
Run compaction
.TP
k2i\-maintenance\-expire\-snapshots(1)
Expire old snapshots
.TP
k2i\-maintenance\-clean\-orphans(1)
Clean up orphan files
.TP
k2i\-maintenance\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
.SH EXTRA
EXAMPLES:
  k2i maintenance compact \-\-config config.toml
  k2i maintenance expire\-snapshots \-\-config config.toml
  k2i maintenance clean\-orphans \-\-config config.toml
